HEADWORD: coracan
<hw>coracan</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an East Indian cereal grass
(<spn>Eleusine coracana</spn>) whose seeds yield a somewhat bitter
flour, a staple in the Orient.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> finger millet, ragi, ragee, African millet, corakan,
kurakkan, <spn>Eleusine coracana</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coracias</ent>⟦br⟧
